content:
Does anybody have an electronic copy of the Makkaifest proceedings?

Bradd Hart, Thomas G. Kucera, Anand Pillay, Philip J. Scott, and Robert A. G. Seely, editors, Models, Logics, and Higher-Dimensional Categories: A Tribute to the Work of MihaÃÅly Makkai, CRM Proceedings and Lecture Notes volume 53. American Mathematical Society, 2011.

(I'm currently looking for Victor Harnik. Model theory vs. categorical logic: Two approaches to pretopos completion (a.k.a. Teq). pp 79-106)
Related: Is the AMS more aggressive than other publishers in getting their publications un-indexed by search engines? I was shocked that I couldn't even find it on libgen

(Also grumble grumble apparently neither the fact that I have forked over money to be an AMS member nor the fact that my university stores a print copy entitles me to download this from the AMS website grumble grumble why is the biggest impediment to my mathematical research at the moment the very professional society which is supposed to be advocating for it grumble grumble)
I'm able to access the complete paper on Google Books: perhaps you will be able to too?

Hmm... that books.google.fr link hangs for me, and on books.google.com https://www.google.com/books/edition/Models_Logics_and_Higher_dimensional_Cat/GT4eswEACAAJ?hl=en the preview is unavailable for me
ah after awhile the fr page loaded, but it says i can't view this page
It's strange: the pages it's possible to preview on Google Books seems different for different people.
Maybe there's a convenient way I could extract the pages to share with you?
im not super familiar with how to extract text from google books -- i'll keep looking and I might end up looking into it and hit you up, thanks!
(Even stranger, I can view the pages in single page format, but not in double page format...)
i'm also sure i have a copy of this on some device, just not one i have immediate access to
I recently decided to delete all my maths files. Luckily I haven't emptied my trash yet. :joy:
@Leopold Schlicht that's a nice paper - thanks!
